           <!-- <h3>Welcome to XIMJ (An Educational Unit of XIDAS, Jabalpur)</h3>-->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12">
            <p style="text-align:justify;">Xavier Institute of Development Action and Studies (XIDAS) was founded in the year 1995 by Fr. Michael Van den Bogaert, SJ. It is a Registered Society run by the Jesuits of Madhya Pradesh Province. It is a sister concern of Jesuit run Management Institutes like XLRI, Jamshedpur; XIM, Bhuwaneshwar; XISS, Ranchi; LIBA, Chennai and XBS, Kolkata and many others across the world.</p>
            <p style="text-align:justify;"></p>
           <p style="text-align:justify;">XIDAS Society proposes to introduce a new Technical Institution (XIMJ) for MBA Course
with specialization in Human Resource, Marketing & Finance and Information Technology, Masters of Business Administration  course aims at preparing the youth to meet the
challenges before the Industry and Corporate  Sector. It aims at creating facilitators and catalysts
who will be engaged in making India a developed nation and to achieve the concept of a welfare
state as visualized by our constitution makers. It also aims at enabling the students to learn about
and adapt the various principles of management and apply it effectively in building a developed
socially responsible and a sustainable society. The course shall provide technical and managerial
expertise in the field of Management and Sustainable development. The prime objective of this
course is to impart theoretical and practical inputs to the students so as to mold   them into
Corporate and Development professionals. It would be a holistic course covering all the technical
and other needs of the corporate as well as development sector and the basic principles and methods
of management. The increasing network of Industry, Corporate, NGOs, funding agencies and other
developmental associations have created a demand for people with technical knowledge and these
offer large-scale employment opportunities in this sector as well.  </p>
